===============================================================
    TestLink 1.6.0 - ReadMe
===============================================================

1. Introduction
===============================================================

    TestLink is a web based test management and test execution system.
    It enables quality assurance teams to create and manage their test 
    cases as well as to organize them into test plans. These test plans 
    allow team members to execute test cases and track test results 
    dynamically.
    
    TestLink is a GPL licensed open source project. All of the source code 
    behind TestLink is freely available for download via SourceForge 
    at http://www.sourceforge.net.If you are interested in contributing 
    to the TestLink effort feel free to contact us.


2. Installation and System Requirements
===============================================================
 
    TestLink environment includes PHP4, MySQL and a Web-server (e.g.  
    functional EasyPHP or XAMP installation).
   
    Download: You can get the newest version at sourceforge.net at 
    https://sourceforge.net/projects/testlink/.
    
    Installation and configuration is described in directory
    <testlink_root>/documentation/installation-manual.html or Installation and
    Configuration manual at http://testlink.sourceforge.net/docs/testlink.php.
   
    Update from previous versions of TestLink : Database schema was
    changed. We recommend to use an installation script. See more 
    in the manual.


3. Release notes
===============================================================
 
    This release is a final release for TestLink 1.6.0. Bug fixing 
    will be applied on this release via 1.6.1, etc. 
    The next development will be provides for 1.7.

	Main new 1.6 features:
	- Requirement based testing
	- Localization
	- Instalator
    See CHANGELOG for more information about new features, bug fixes 
    and changes.


4. Known problems
===============================================================

    - No blocking issue is known at the time.
    - Several minor issues are listed in TestLink Bug Tracking System.
    

5. Bug Reports and Feedback
===============================================================

    The Bug Overview on the TestLink web site lets you search for and
    examine existing bug reports, submit your own bug reports, and tell us
    which bug fixes matter most to you. To submit a bug or a feature, please 
    use our  Mantis installation at http://www.testlink.org/mantis/ for 
    TestLink. 
    
    You can see ther also the current bugs and requests.You may also contact 
    us at the TestLink forum at http://www.testlink.org/tiki/tiki-forums.php.
    
    